subject: p12475198
Findings: Right PICC line ends at mid SVC. Left-sided pacer defibrillator with leads through the left transvenous approach is seen to end in the right atrium, right ventricle, and coronary sinus. Minimal right basal atelectasis is unchanged. There are no other lung opacities of concern. Top normal heart size, mediastinal and hilar contours are stable.
Impression: Right PICC line ends at mid SVC. Small bibasilar atelectasis is unchanged.
